columns.name: name
columns.description: The name that you assigned to the Resolver endpoint when you submitted a CreateResolverEndpoint.

columns.name: id
columns.description: The ID of the Resolver endpoint.

columns.name: arn
columns.description: The ARN (Amazon Resource Name) for the Resolver endpoint.

columns.name: creation_time
columns.description: The date and time that the endpoint was created, in Unix time format and Coordinated Universal Time (UTC).

columns.name: creator_request_id
columns.description: A unique string that identifies the request that created the Resolver endpoint.The CreatorRequestId allows failed requests to be retried without the risk of executing the operation twice.

columns.name: direction
columns.description: Indicates whether the Resolver endpoint allows inbound or outbound DNS queries.

columns.name: host_vpc_id
columns.description: The ID of the VPC that you want to create the Resolver endpoint in.

columns.name: ip_address_count
columns.description: The number of IP addresses that the Resolver endpoint can use for DNS queries.

columns.name: modification_time
columns.description: The date and time that the endpoint was last modified, in Unix time format and Coordinated Universal Time (UTC).

columns.name: status
columns.description: A code that specifies the current status of the Resolver endpoint.

columns.name: status_message
columns.description: A detailed description of the status of the Resolver endpoint.

columns.name: ip_addresses
columns.description: Information about the IP addresses in your VPC that DNS queries originate from (for outbound endpoints) or that you forward DNS queries to (for inbound endpoints).

columns.name: security_group_ids
columns.description: The ID of one or more security groups that control access to this VPC.

columns.name: tags_src
columns.description: A list of tags assigned to the Resolver endpoint.
